  "track_info": "Darlington Raceway is a 1.366-mile (2.198 km) egg-shaped oval in Darlington, South Carolina — nicknamed \"The Lady in Black\" and \"The Track Too Tough to Tame.\" The oldest superspeedway in NASCAR, Darlington opened in 1950 and its unusual asymmetrical shape is a direct legacy of a minnow pond the previous landowner refused to relocate during construction — turns 1–2 are wide and sweeping while turns 3–4 are tight and pinched, making it nearly impossible to find a setup that works equally well at both ends. The race runs 147 laps across three stages — 45, 45, and 57 laps respectively — for a total distance of approximately 200.8 miles. Corey Heim is the defending race winner, having taken victory here in 2025. The all-time race lap record belongs to Bobby Hamilton at 133.645 mph (March 14, 2003), while the qualifying record was set by Cole Whitt at 173.933 mph (March 12, 2011)."
}

